ting the door.";i:12;s:102:"We recommend getting help opening holding it in place while you move the car in and then lowering the.";i:13;s:55:"Do not cut any holes unless you just like fixing holes.";i:14;s:62:"There is no need for a hole to pop the emergency release cord.";i:15;s:83:"There are two simple ways to disconnect the machine from the door from the outside.";i:16;s:33:"Garage doors are not very secure.";i:17;s:51:"You will need three tools a 4ft ladder or taller a.";i:18;s:86:"When your garage door doesnt open with the remote a few things can cause this problem.";i:19;s:26:"You might be out of range.";i:20;s:69:"The antenna on the motor could be damaged or blocked from the signal.";i:21;s:44:"Make sure it is hanging down from the motor.";i:22;s:41:"If the door opens with the wall switch a.";i:23;s:22:"Ok Solved the problem.";i:24;s:94:"There are 4 bolts on the outside of the garage door holding the opening mechanism to the door.";i:25;s:120:"I undid them and the coupling holding the opening mechanism to the door let go and I was able to manually open the door.";i:26;s:33:"Check the manual for your opener.";i:27;s:42:"But back to the problem of how to open it.";i:28;s:171:"If the garage does not have an alternative access there should be a manual cable release which disconnects the door from the opener chain so that you can manually open it.";i:29;s:63:"Often this is in the form of a small key near your garage door.";i:30;s:17:"August 19th 2011.";i:31;s:101:"My garage door remotes will not open door from the outside unless you are right in front of the door.";i:32;s:69:"I have replaced the battery on reprogrammed the remotes with no luck.";i:33;s:67:"Both remotes will open door from inside garage as will wall switch.";i:34;s:60:"I have also checked to see that the antenna is hanging down.";i:35;s:43:"Open a Locked Garage Door from the Outside.";i:36;s:157:"When you find yourself pressing the buttons of your garage door to open the same yet nothing is workin